pan\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003ePruitt\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eGrudin\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2003\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003ePersonas: practice and theory\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eProceedings of the 2003 Conference on Designing for User Experiences\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e1\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e15\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eNew York, NY\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eACM\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/997078.997089\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_053_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac53Aa\\\"\\u003ePruitt \\u0026amp; Grudin, 2003\\u003c/a\\u003e), meaning the data were manually gathered and then manually analyzed to develop the personas (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_052_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac52Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003ePruitt, J., \\u0026amp; Adlin, T. (2006). \\u003citalic\\u003eThe Persona Lifecycle: Keeping People in Mind Throughout Product Design\\u003c/italic\\u003e (1st ed.). San Francisco, CA: Morgan Kaufmann.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003ePruitt\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAdlin\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eT.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2006\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe Persona Lifecycle: Keeping People in Mind Throughout Product Design\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e1st ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eSan Francisco, CA\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eMorgan Kaufmann\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_052_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac52Aa\\\"\\u003ePruitt \\u0026amp; Adlin, 2006\\u003c/a\\u003e).\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eFrom their inception in the late 1980s, refinement in the early 1990s (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_015_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac15Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eCooper, A. (2004). \\u003citalic\\u003eThe inmates are running the asylum: Why high-tech products drive us crazy and how to restore the sanity\\u003c/italic\\u003e (2nd ed.). Indianapolis: Pearson Higher Education.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eCooper\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2004\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe inmates are running the asylum: Why high-tech products drive us crazy and how to restore the sanity\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e2nd ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eIndianapolis\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003ePearson Higher Education\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_015_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac15Aa\\\"\\u003eCooper, 2004\\u003c/a\\u003e), and following decades of use, personas were generally \u201cflat media\u201d (i.e., presented on paper or in an electronic document), encompassed within a one-page or a two-page summary called a persona profile (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_049_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac49Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eNielsen, L., \\u0026amp; Storgaard Hansen, K. (2014). Personas is applicable: a study on the use of personas in Denmark. \\u003citalic\\u003eProceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems\\u003c/italic\\u003e (pp. 1665\u20131674). New York, NY: ACM. doi:\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/2556288.2557080\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eNielsen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eL.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eStorgaard Hansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eK.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2014\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003ePersonas is applicable: a study on the use of personas in Denmark\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eProceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e1665\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e1674\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eNew York, NY\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eACM\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/2556288.2557080\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_049_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac49Aa\\\"\\u003eNielsen \\u0026amp; Storgaard Hansen, 2014\\u003c/a\\u003e). A persona profile generally (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_001_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1ab4Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 1\\u003c/a\\u003e\\u003cfn id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fn_001_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1ab3b6Aa\\\" symbol=\\\"1\\\"\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eCredit: See \\u003cext-link xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" ext-link-type=\\\"uri\\\" xlink:href=\\\"https://www.ibm.com/garage/method/practices/think/practice_personas/\\\"\\u003ehttps://www.ibm.com/garage/method/practices/think/practice_personas/\\u003c/ext-link\\u003e.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/fn\\u003e) contains an assortment of attributes concerning the persona, including name, gender, age, goals, demographic attributes, pain points, a headshot image, a quote, and so on. As such, from their initial inception through numerous decades of use, personas were primarily data structures\u2014not interactive decision-making tools. A persona profile was a mechanism to organize the data concerning the imaginary person to present the information that decision-makers and others leverage to accomplish their goals of better targeting customers/users/audiences.\\u003cfn id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fn_002_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1ab3b8Aa\\\" symbol=\\\"2\\\"\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eNote \u2013 For brevity, we generally use the term \u201cuser\u201d in the manuscript but imply also customer or audience.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/fn\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cfigure id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_001_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1ab4Aa\\\" position=\\\"float\\\" fig-type=\\\"figure\\\"\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eFigure 1\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cfigCaption\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eExample of a traditional flat-file persona profile.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/figCaption\\u003e\\u003cimg xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"graphic/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_001.jpg\\\" src=\\\"https://sciendo-parsed-data-feed.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/6005bbb5e797941b18f255fd/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_001.jpg?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Date=20211130T193832Z\\u0026amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Expires=18000\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Credential=AKIA6AP2G7AKDOZOEZ7H%2F20211130%2Feu-central-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Signature=b0a73b863f941741aaa8261bd6304cf7e2aafad8a70e0fd10c5562a804b35a0f\\\" class=\\\"mw-100\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/img\\u003e\\u003c/figure\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eHowever, the advent of online web, social media (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_032_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac32Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eKhan, F., Si, X., \\u0026amp; Khan, K. U. (2019). Social media affordances and information sharing: An evidence from Chinese public organizations. \\u003citalic\\u003eData and Information Management\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e3\\u003c/italic\\u003e(3), 135\u2013154.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKhan\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eF.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSi\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eX.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKhan\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eK. 