c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2019\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eBig data adoption: State of the art and research challenges\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eInformation Processing \\u0026amp; Management\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e56\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e6\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1016/j.ipm.2019.102095\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_006_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ab6Aa\\\"\\u003eBaig, Shuib, \\u0026amp; Yadegaridehkordi, 2019\\u003c/a\\u003e) platforms allows for the possibility of data-driven personas that are created algorithmically (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_004_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ab4Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eAn, J., Kwak, H., Salminen, J., Jung, S., \\u0026amp; Jansen, B. J. (2018). Imaginary people representing real numbers: Generating personas from online social media data. \\u003citalic\\u003eACM Transactions on the Web (TWEB)\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e12\\u003c/italic\\u003e(4), 1\u201326.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAn\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKwak\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eH.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2018\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eImaginary people representing real numbers: Generating personas from online social media data\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eACM Transactions on the Web (TWEB)\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e12\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e4\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e1\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e26\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_004_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ab4Aa\\\"\\u003eAn, Kwak, Jung, Salminen, \\u0026amp; Jansen, 2018\\u003c/a\\u003e) and enable interaction between decision-makers and the persona information. Compared to a flat file, these personas provide an interface to an integrated full-stack persona analytics system, along the conceptual lines of task integration (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_009_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ab9Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eBystr\u00f6m, K., \\u0026amp; Kumpulainen, S. (2020). Vertical and horizontal relationships amongst task-based information needs. \\u003citalic\\u003eInformation Processing \\u0026amp; Management, 57\\u003c/italic\\u003e(2). doi:\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1016/j.ipm.2019.102065\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eBystr\u00f6m\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eK.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKumpulainen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2020\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eVertical and horizontal relationships amongst task-based information needs\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eInformation Processing \\u0026amp; Management\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e57\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1016/j.ipm.2019.102065\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_009_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ab9Aa\\\"\\u003eBystr\u00f6m \\u0026amp; Kumpulainen, 2020\\u003c/a\\u003e) that contains individual user data to the persona profile (i.e., from backend user data to frontend user conceptualization). Rather than a flat file, for these systems, the persona profile serves as a system interface, serving as both a data structure and equip the stakeholders with data interactivity. However, despite the availability of online data, there have been few data-driven persona systems to date.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThus, in this research, we conceptually explore the relationship between personas (as \\u003citalic\\u003etools to understand people\\u003c/italic\\u003e) and analytics (as \\u003citalic\\u003esystems to accomplish tasks\\u003c/italic\\u003e), using digital marketing use cases to exemplify the strengths of data-driven personas amidst analytics use cases by examining specific use cases pertaining to digital marketing. This positioning is reflected in \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_002_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1ab7Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 2\\u003c/a\\u003e.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cfigure id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_002_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1ab7Aa\\\" position=\\\"float\\\" fig-type=\\\"figure\\\"\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eFigure 2\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cfigCaption\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eConceptual positioning of the persona \u2013 analytics integration research.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/figCaption\\u003e\\u003cimg xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"graphic/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_002.jpg\\\" src=\\\"https://sciendo-parsed-data-feed.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/6005bbb5e797941b18f255fd/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_002.jpg?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Date=20211130T193832Z\\u0026amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Expires=18000\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Credential=AKIA6AP2G7AKDOZOEZ7H%2F20211130%2Feu-central-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Signature=e8d11230fb6383d9325ecf965b5bea4816a342f5e9829b6d8956461124844bd1\\\" class=\\\"mw-100\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/img\\u003e\\u003c/figure\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eWhile there have been attempts to \u201cmodernize\u201d personas by automating their creation and tying the concept to behavioral online analytics data (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_021_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac21Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eHammou, B. A., Lahcen, A. A., \\u0026amp; Mouline, S. (2020). Towards a real-time processing framework based on improved distributed recurrent neural network variants with fastText for social big data analytics. \\u003citalic\\u003eInformation Processing \\u0026amp; Management, 57\\u003c/italic\\u003e(1). doi:\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1016/j.ipm.2019.102122\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eHammou\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. A.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eLahcen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA. A.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eMouline\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2020\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eTowards a real-time processing framework based on improved distributed recurrent neural network variants with fastText for social big data analytics\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eInformation Processing \\u0026amp; Management\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e57\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e1\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1016/j.ipm.2019.102122\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_021_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac21Aa\\\"\\u003eHammou, Lahcen, \\u0026amp; Mouline, 2020\\u003c/a\\u003e), the question remains: \\u003citalic\\u003ecan data-driven personas offer efficiency and/or effectiveness value relative to other analytics approaches and data representations for user understanding tasks?\\u003c/italic\\u003e This question remains largely unaddressed in the previous research, even for personas in general, and it serves as the motivation for the research presented here. Overall, there is surprisingly little research in the field of marketing, HCI, or information science about data granularity in user segmentation. Yet, this is an issue that is practically important and theoretically interesting. Notably, customer segmentation and granularity are discussed by \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j