03eProceedings of the 2017 CHI Conference Extended Abstracts on Human Factors in Computing Systems\\u003c/italic\\u003e (pp. 1748\u20131755). New York, NY: ACM. doi:\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/3027063.3053120\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS. G.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAn\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKwak\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eH.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAhmad\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eM.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eNielsen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eL.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2017\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003ePersona Generation from Aggregated Social Media Data\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eProceedings of the 2017 CHI Conference Extended Abstracts on Human Factors in Computing Systems\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e1748\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e1755\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eNew York, NY\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eACM\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/3027063.3053120\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_028_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac28Aa\\\"\\u003eJung, An, Kwak, Ahmad, Nielsen, \\u0026amp; Jansen, 2017\\u003c/a\\u003e), a robust full-stack persona system to illustrate the functional capabilities of a data-driven persona system at three levels of granularity: data (i.e., the user), analytics (i.e., percentages, probabilities, and weights of segments), and conceptualization (i.e., the personas profiles). Data-driven and algorithmic-based persona generation systems can drastically improve the process of persona creation, how to use persona profiles, and the conceptualization of persona profiles as design tools, along with providing enhancements to the user of analytics. The persona creation and generation process are now shifting from manual creation to data-driven generation. The result is that the created persona profile is linked to the underlying user data, ranging from the aggregated to the individual level. As such, the persona concept is changed from a flat data structure document to an interactive interface for the underlying analytics system. This new framework offers a merging of personas and analytics; rather than competition, these two are now viewed as complements. Yet, there are still contexts for traditionally developed personas and for the employment of analytics in a pure form.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eWe begin with a short literature review for the positioning of data-driven personas within the broader context of personas in general and analytics. We then discuss a sampling of digital marketing use cases to show the need for data-driven personas. Then, we present a data-driven persona system that integrates personas with analytics. We end with the discussion and implications of the role of data-driven personas for digital marketing.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/sec\\u003e\\u003csec id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_s_002_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003e2\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cdiv\\u003ePositioning Based on Related Literature\\u003c/div\\u003e\\u003csec id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_s_002_s_001_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1b2Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003e2.1\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cdiv\\u003eRelationship between Personas and User Segmentation\\u003c/div\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe concept of personas is employed within many fields, industries, and domains (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_015_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac15Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eCooper, A. (2004). \\u003citalic\\u003eThe inmates are running the asylum: Why high-tech products drive us crazy and how to restore the sanity\\u003c/italic\\u003e (2nd ed.). Indianapolis: Pearson Higher Education.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eCooper\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2004\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe inmates are running the asylum: Why high-tech products drive us crazy and how to restore the sanity\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e2nd ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eIndianapolis\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003ePearson Higher Education\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_015_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac15Aa\\\"\\u003eCooper, 2004\\u003c/a\\u003e; \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_