u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ. K.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKim\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eN.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSrivastava\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eR. K.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e1998\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eMarket orientation and organizational performance: Is innovation a missing link?\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eJournal of Marketing\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e62\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e4\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e30\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e45\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_022_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac22Aa\\\"\\u003eHan, Kim, \\u0026amp; Srivastava, 1998\\u003c/a\\u003e). According to our view, personas can help by providing operationalization of the market orientation concept. It is easy to see personas could be of help here, as they provide a customer-oriented frame of reference that requires little analytical sophistication from decision-makers and can, therefore, be applied at all levels of the organization.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eIn organizations, personas are applied at different levels, for example, by customer service at the operative customer interface, designers and developers in product lifecycle planning, and by executives at the strategic corporate level who desire to craft strategic agendas that are aligned with underlying market trends (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_034_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac34Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eKohli, A. K., \\u0026amp; Jaworski, B. J. (1990). Market orientation: The construct, research propositions, and managerial implications. \\u003citalic\\u003eJournal of Marketing\\u003c/italic\\u003e, 54(2), 1\u201318.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKohli\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA. K.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJaworski\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e1990\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eMarket orientation: The construct, research propositions, and managerial implications\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eJournal of Marketing\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e54\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e1\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e18\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_034_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac34Aa\\\"\\u003eKohli \\u0026amp; Jaworski 1990\\u003c/a\\u003e). This enables the decision-makers to understand experiences and backgrounds different from their own, supporting the realization that the preferences of the users most likely differ from those working inside the organizational bubble (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_044_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac44Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eMiaskiewicz, T., \\u0026amp; Kozar, K. A. (2011). Personas and user-centered design: How can personas benefit product design processes? \\u003citalic\\u003eDesign Studies\\u003c/italic\\