3e, \\u003citalic\\u003e4\\u003c/italic\\u003e(2), 47\u201365.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAn\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKwak\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eH.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS. G.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2018\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eAre personas done? Evaluating their usefulness in the age of digital analytics\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003ePersona Studies\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e4\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e47\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e65\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_058_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac58Aa\\\"\\u003eSalminen, Jansen, An, Kwak, \\u0026amp; Jung, 2018\\u003c/a\\u003e) (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_003_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1b3b3Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 3\\u003c/a\\u003e for illustration). However, personalization is not the same as understanding the user. For example, a recommendation algorithm may personalize product suggestions for a given customer in such an effective manner that the user generally accepts the recommendation. However, this does not necessarily imply that the user is happy or pleased with the overall customer service.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cfigure id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_003_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1b3b3Aa\\\" position=\\\"float\\\" fig-type=\\\"figure\\\"\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eFigure 3\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cfigCaption\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eAlgorithmic ad targeting and optimization (adapted from \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_064_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac64Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eSmith, S. (2015). \\u003citalic\\u003eThe Benefits of Machine Learning and Programmatic Buying\\u003c/italic\\u003e [Marketing]. Retrieved from \\u003curi\\u003ehttps://www.slideshare.net/Intelligent_Optimisations/the-benefits-of-machine-learning-and-programmatic-buying\\u003c/uri\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"web\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSmith\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2015\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe Benefits of Machine Learning and Programmatic Buying\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"comment\\\"\\u003e[Marketing]. Retrieved from \\u003curi\\u003ehttps://www.slideshare.net/Intelligent_Optimisations/the-benefits-of-machine-learning-and-programmatic-buying\\u003c/uri\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_064_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac64Aa\\\"\\u003eSmith, 2015\\u003c/a\\u003e).\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/figCaption\\u003e\\u003cimg xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"graphic/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_003.jpg\\\" src=\\\"https://sciendo-parsed-data-feed.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/6005bbb5e797941b18f255fd/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_003.jpg?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Date=20211130T193832Z\\u0026amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Expires=18000\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Credential=AKIA6AP2G7AKDOZOEZ7H%2F20211130%2Feu-central-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Signature=969e252062c2c10ce417c8fae8c7f1070348d673d9b37ec404f1b44cf410bfbe\\\" class=\\\"mw-100\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/img\\u003e\\u003c/figure\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe machine finds the higher performance subgroups from the target audience. Prior information, such as the marketer\u2019s experience or use of personas can also be used to narrow down the search space.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eConversely, since their initial inception, personas have typically been flat structures, either in the form of actual paper or in the form of an electronic PDF-like documents, and they served as mainly data structures that presented present assorted bits of data into usable information for decision-makers or implementors. Partly due to this flat data structure, personas have come under substantial criticism for being of limited practical value within the actual design process (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_011_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac11Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eChapman, C. N., \\u0026amp; Milham, R. P. (2006). The Personas\u2019 New Clothes: Methodological and Practical Arguments against a Popular Method. In \\u003citalic\\u003eProceedings of the Human Factors and Ergonomics Society 50nd Annual Meeting\\u003c/italic\\u003e (Vol. 50, No. 5, pp. 634\u2013636), Los Angeles, CA: SAGE Publications. doi:\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1177/154193120605000503\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"