\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2003\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003ePersonas: practice and theory\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eProceedings of the 2003 Conference on Designing for User Experiences\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e1\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e15\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eNew York, NY\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eACM\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/997078.997089\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_053_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac53Aa\\\"\\u003ePruitt \\u0026amp; Grudin, 2003\\u003c/a\\u003e), when using customer data has even been employed at all in the persona creation process. As the number of participants in focus groups is usually small and noted issues with survey data (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_058_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac58Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eSalminen, J., Jansen, B. J., An, J., Kwak, H., \\u0026amp; Jung, S. G. (2018). Are personas done? Evaluating their usefulness in the age of digital analytics. \\u003citalic\\u003ePersona Studies\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e4\\u003c/italic\\u003e(2), 47\u201365.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAn\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKwak\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eH.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS. G.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2018\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eAre personas done? Evaluating their usefulness in the age of digital analytics\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003ePersona Studies\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e4\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e47\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e65\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_058_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac58Aa\\\"\\u003eSalminen et al., 2018\\u003c/a\\u003e), this has led to the employment of mainly qualitative data analysis approaches that lead end users to question if the underlying persona data is representative, updated, or valid of the actual user population. However, the advent of data-driven personas in the age of easily available analytics data has led to a recognition of the possible integration of the personas (to give a human face) and analytics (to provide actionable numbers and precision).\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eRemarkably, with the combining of personas and analytics, the strengths of each approach help offset the deficiencies of the other. Conceptually, personas are easy for people to understand and generate empathy for the user, but personas are perceived as not granular and not actionable. Analytics data can be granular and actionable, but analytics can be cumbersome for employment and difficult for end users to comprehend. Nonetheless, the combination of both leverages the strengths and limits the weakness of each, as shown in (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_057_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac57Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eSalminen, J., Guan, K., Nielsen, L., Jung, S., Chowdhury, S. A., \\u0026amp; Jansen, B. J. (2020, July 19). A Template for Data-Driven Personas: Analyzing 31 Quantitatively Oriented Persona Profiles. \\u003citalic\\u003eIn Proceedings of the 22nd International Conference on Human-Computer Interaction (HCII\u201920)\\u003c/italic\\u003e. In-press.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"confproc\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eGuan\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eK.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eNielsen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eL.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eChowdhury\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS. A.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2020\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cmonth\\u003eJuly\\u003c/month\\u003e\\u003cday\\u003e19\\u003c/day\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eA Template for Data-Driven Personas: Analyzing 31 Quantitatively Oriented Persona Profiles\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"comment\\\"\\u003eIn\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cconf-name\\u003eProceedings of the 22nd International Conference on Human-Computer Interaction (HCII\u201920)\\u003c/conf-name\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"comment\\\"\\u003eIn-press.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_057_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac57Aa\\\"\\u003eSalminen, Guan, Nielsen, Jung, Chowdhury, \\u0026amp; Jansen, 2020\\u003c/a\\u003e). Personas that are automatically generated from analytics data have all the strength of standard personas, and, when serving as the interface to analytics systems, they provide all of the strengths of user analytics, as illustrated in \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_004_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1b3b7Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 4\\u003c/a\\u003e.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cfigure id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_004_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1b3b7Aa\\\" position=\\\"float\\\" fig-type=\\\"figure\\\"\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eFigure 4\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cfigCaption\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eAttributes of manual persona generation and automatic persona generation.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/figCaption\\u003e\\u003cimg xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"graphic/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_004.jpg\\\" src=\\\"https://sciendo-parsed-data-feed.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/6005bbb5e797941b18f255fd/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_004.jpg?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Date=20211130T193832Z\\u0026amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Expires=18000\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Credential=AKIA6AP2G7AKDOZOEZ7H%2F20211130%2Feu-central-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Signature=8c2e70c7de1298efc383206740e029eaddc30288387719b10591edc09511df3d\\\" class=\\\"mw-100\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/img\\u003e\\u003c/figure\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eSince personas were first introduced, a range of other online analytics platforms, services, and tools have emerged (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_015_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac15Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eCooper, A. (2004). \\u003citalic\\u003eThe inmates are running the asylum: Why high-tech products drive us crazy and how to restore the sanity\\u003c/italic\\u003e (2nd ed.). Indianapolis: Pearson Higher Education.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eCooper\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2004\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe inmates are running the asylum: Why high-tech products drive us crazy and how to restore the sanity\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e2nd ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eIndianapolis\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003ePearson Higher Education\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_015_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac15Aa\\\"\\u003eCooper, 2004\\u003c/a\\u003e; \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_029_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac29Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eJung, S. G., Salminen, J., An, J., Kwak, H., \\u0026amp; Jansen, B. J. (2018). Automatically Conceptualizing Social Media Analytics Data via Personas. \\u003citalic\\u003eProceedings of the International AAAI Conference on Web and Social Media (ICWSM 2018)\\u003c/italic\\u003e, 715\u2013716.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"confproc\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS. G.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAn\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKwak\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eH.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2018\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eAutomatically Conceptualizing Social Media Analytics Data via Personas\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cconf-name\\u003eProceedings of the International AAAI Conference on Web and Social Media (ICWSM 2018)\\u003c/conf-name\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e715\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e716\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_029_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac29Aa\\\"\\u003eJung, Salminen, An, Kwak, \\u0026amp; Jansen, 2018\\u003c/a\\u003e; \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_065_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac65Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eSpringer, A., \\u0026amp; Whittaker, S. (2019). Progressive disclosure: Empirically motivated approaches to designing effective transparency. \\u003citalic\\u003eProceedings of the 24th International Conference on Intelligent User Interfaces\\u003c/italic\\u003e (pp. 107\u2013120). New York, NY: ACM. doi:\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/3301275.3302322\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSpringer\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eWhittaker\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2019\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eProgressive disclosure: Empirically motivated approaches to designing effective transparency\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eProceedings of the 24th International Conference on Intelligent User Interfaces\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e107\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e120\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eNew York, NY\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eACM\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/3301275.3302322\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_065_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac65Aa\\\"\\u003eSpringer \\u0026amp; Whittaker, 2019\\u003c/a\\u003e) - including Adobe Analytics, IBM Analytics, Facebook Insights, Google Analytics\u2014as well as integrating services (e.g., HootSuite, Tableau, etc.) that organizations can use to understand their users and user segments. These tools provide organizations with access to both individual users and aggregated users\u2019 big data, resulting in further questioning about the value of using traditional qualitative personas for user insights.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eAs such, there is a critical need for the updating of the persona creation concept and the use of analytics through the employment and use of data-driven personas that are created algorithmically using large quantities of user data and then presenting these personas as interfaces to fully functional interactive analytics systems for user understanding.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/sec\\u003e\\u003csec id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_s_002_s_003_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1b4Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003e2.3\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cdiv\\u003eConceptual Analysis of Personas for Digital Marketing\\u003c/div\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eAs an illustration of the employment of data-driven personas, we present their employment through a use case approach in the domain of digital marketing.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eDigital marketing embodies several techniques to get a response from their target customers. Drawing from prior studies on digital marketing, we define digital marketing use cases. A \u201cuse case\u201d is defined as an activity that the marketer has control over, which is important in achieving marketing goals, and that covers the full spectrum of the first touch to purchase by the consumers (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_038_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac38Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eLemon, K. N., \\u0026amp; Verhoef, P. C. (2016). Understanding customer experience throughout the customer journey. \\u003citalic\\u003eJournal of Marketing\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e80\\u003c/italic\\u003e(6), 69\u201396.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eLemon\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eK. N.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eVerhoef\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eP. C.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2016\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eUnderstanding customer experience throughout the customer journey\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eJournal of Marketing\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e80\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e6\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e69\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e96\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_038_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac38Aa\\\"\\u003eLemon \\u0026amp; Verhoef, 2016\\u003c/a\\u003e). Particularly, (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_014_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac14Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eConstantinides, E. (2004). Influencing the online consumer\u2019s behavior: The Web experience. \\u003citalic\\u003eInternet Research\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e14\\u003c/italic\\u003e(2), 111\u2013126.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eConstantinides\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eE.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2004\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eInfluencing the online consumer\u2019s behavior: The Web experience\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eInternet Research\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e14\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e111\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e126\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_014_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac14Aa\\\"\\u003eConstantinides, 2004\\u003c/a\\u003e) (p. 113) refers to \u201cWeb experience\u201d that \u201cembraces elements like searching, browsing, finding, selecting, comparing and evaluating information as well as interacting and transacting with the online firm.\u201d As such, it is essential to define the use cases of digital marketing in relation to online user behavior. \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"table\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_tab_002_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b1b4b4Aa\\\"\\u003eTable 2\\u003c/a\\u003e depicts digital marketing use cases found from the literature, with a more complete systemic review presented in (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_058_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac58Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eSalminen, J., Jansen, B. J., An, J., Kwak, H., \\u0026amp; Jung, S. G. (2018). Are personas done? Evaluating their usefulness in the age of digital analytics. \\u003citalic\\u003ePersona Studies\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e4\\u003c/italic\\u003e(2), 47\u201365.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAn\\u003c/span\\u