 the relationship between targeting and message creation.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eOnce visitors are attracted to the target destination (e.g., website and mobile app), other tactics follow to achieve conversion, the final outcome of online interaction (Pitt, Berthon \\u0026amp; Watson, 1996). According to (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_014_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac14Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eConstantinides, E. (2004). Influencing the online consumer\u2019s behavior: The Web experience. \\u003citalic\\u003eInternet Research\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e14\\u003c/italic\\u003e(2), 111\u2013126.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eConstantinides\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eE.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2004\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eInfluencing the online consumer\u2019s behavior: The Web experience\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eInternet Research\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e14\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e111\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e126\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_014_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac14Aa\\\"\\u003eConstantinides, 2004\\u003c/a\\u003e), the decision-making processes of online users can be influenced by the creation and delivery of Web experiences, comprising information content, perceptual cues and stimuli, and offerings. The methods of dynamic pricing are used to achieve the optimal pricing strategy; for example, airlines may set their prices based on customer