u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eK.-J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eEdvardsson\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSundstr\u00f6m\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eE.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAndersson\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eP.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2010\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eA customer-dominant logic of service\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eJournal of Service Management\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e21\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e4\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e531\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e548\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_067_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac67Aa\\\"\\u003eStauss, Heinonen, Strandvik, Mickelsson, Edvardsson, Sundstr\u00f6m, \\u0026amp; Andersson, 2010\\u003c/a\\u003e). By influencing the level of motivation and empathy, personas can also influence actions taken by individuals at different organizational levels and, thus, become a vehicle for a higher degree of market orientation within the organization employing them.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/sec\\u003e\\u003csec id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_s_004_s_004_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b3b6Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003e4.4\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cdiv\\u003eScope of Both Personas and Analytics within the Confines of Decision-making\\u003c/div\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe question then becomes: \\u003citalic\\u003eWhat decisions are the individuals making?\\u003c/italic\\u003e Obviously, the answer depends on several factors, notably the industry, organizational context, and the position of the decision-maker. Here, we have based our list of decision tasks in digital marketing. Even in this context, characterized by rapid innovation and technology as a driving force, personas seem to have their role. When dealing with a representation of a person, the interaction between personas and the users of analytics systems becomes evident. The users in these situations often use terms such as \u2018she is interested in...\u201d, \u2018she likes...\u201d. Such verbalization is not usually heard when speaking of data; for numbers, the interpretation tends to be fewer personas (\u201cthey are...,\u201d etc.). The scope forcefully becomes more general and loses the appeal of individual characteristics. The second argument, consequently, is to define the scope of personas, more needs to be known of the decision-makers. As such, there are several areas for future research, as discussed in (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_029_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac29Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eJung, S. G., Salminen, J., An, J., Kwak, H., \\u0026amp; Jansen, B. J. (2018). Automatically Conceptualizing Social Media Analytics Data via Personas. \\u003citalic\\u003eProceedings of the International AAAI Conference on Web and Social Media (ICWSM 2018)\\u003c/italic\\u003e, 715\u2013716.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"confproc\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS. G.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\