re design (<a data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\"bibr\" data-tooltip-info='<span class=\"ref\"  id=\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_043_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac43Aa\"><span class=\"mixed-citation\">Marshall, R., Cook, S., Mitchell, V., Summerskill, S., Haines, V., Maguire, M., \u2026 &amp; Case, K. (2015). Design and evaluation: End users, user datasets and personas. <italic>Applied Ergonomics, 46</italic>, 311\u2013317.</span><span class=\"element-citation\"  publication-type=\"journal\" publication-format=\"print\"><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Marshall</span><span class=\"given-names\">R.</span></span><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Cook</span><span class=\"given-names\">S.</span></span><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Mitchell</span><span class=\"given-names\">V.</span></span><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Summerskill</span><span class=\"given-names\">S.</span></span><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Haines</span><span class=\"given-names\">V.</span></span><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Maguire</span><span class=\"given-names\">M.</span></span><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Case</span><span class=\"given-names\">K.</span></span><year>2015</year><article-title>Design and evaluation: End users, user datasets and personas</article-title><span class=\"source\">Applied Ergonomics</span><volume>46</volume><span class=\"fpage\">311</span><span class=\"lpage\">317</span></span></span>' href=\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_043_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac43Aa\">Marshall et al., 2015</a>), among an abundance of others. Most user-facing organizations have personas at some level of planning and usage. There are many claimed benefits of personas (<a data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\"bibr\" data-tooltip-info='<span class=\"ref\"  id=\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_017_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac17Aa\"><span class=\"mixed-citation\">Drego, V. L., Dorsey, M., Burns, M., &amp; Catino, S. (2010). <italic>The ROI Of Personas</italic