nference on Human Factors in Computing Systems</span><span class=\"fpage\">2677</span><span class=\"lpage\">2686</span><span class=\"publisher-loc\">New York, NY</span><publisher-name>ACM</publisher-name><pub-id style=\"display:none;\"  pub-id-type=\"doi\">10.1145/2470654.2481370</pub-id></span></span>' href=\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_019_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac19Aa\">Eriksson, Artman, &amp; Swartling, 2013</a>; <a data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\"bibr\" data-tooltip-info='<span class=\"ref\"  id=\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_020_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac20Aa\"><span class=\"mixed-citation\">Friess, E. (2012). Personas and decision making in the design process: an ethnographic case study. <italic>Proceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems</italic> (pp. 1209\u20131218). New York, NY: ACM. doi:<pub-id style=\"display:none;\"  pub-id-type=\"doi\">10.1145/2207676.2208572</pub-id></span><span class=\"element-citation\"  publication-type=\"book\" publication-format=\"print\"><span class=\"name\"><span class=\"surname\">Friess</span><span class=\"given-names\">E.</span></span><year>2012</year><article-title>Personas and decision making in the design process: an ethnographic case study</article-title><span class=\"source\">Proceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems</span><span class=\"fpage\">1209</span><span class=\"lpage\">1218</span><span class=\"publisher-loc\">New York, NY</span><publisher-name>ACM</publisher-name><pub-id style=\"display:none;\"  pub-id-type=\"doi\">10.1145/2207676.2208572</pub-id></span></span>' href=\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_020_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac20Aa\">Friess, 2012</a>; <a data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\"bibr\" data-tooltip-info='<span class=\"ref\"  id=\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_044_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac44Aa\"><span class=\"mixed-citation\">Miaskiewicz, T., &amp; Kozar, K. A. (2011). Personas and user-centered design: How can personas benefit product design processes? <italic>Design Studies</italic>, 