ly generated from qualitative data gathered from surveys, focus groups, or related data collection methods (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_045_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac45Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eMiaskiewicz, T., \\u0026amp; Luxmoore, C. (2017). The use of data-driven personas to facilitate organizational adoption\u2013A case study. \\u003citalic\\u003eThe Design Journal\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e20\\u003c/italic\\u003e(3), 357\u2013374.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eMiaskiewicz\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eT.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eLuxmoore\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eC.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2017\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eThe use of data-driven personas to facilitate organizational adoption\u2013A case study\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe Design Journal\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e20\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e3\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e357\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e374\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_045_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac45Aa\\\"\\u003eMiaskiewicz \\u0026amp; Luxmoore, 2017\\u003c/a\\u003e; \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_053_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac53Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003ePruitt, J., \\u0026amp; Grudin, J. (2003). Persona