out Product Design\\u003c/italic\\u003e (1st ed.). San Francisco, CA: Morgan Kaufmann.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003ePruitt\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAdlin\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eT.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2006\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe Persona Lifecycle: Keeping People in Mind Throughout Product Design\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e1st ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eSan Francisco, CA\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eMorgan Kaufmann\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_052_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac52Aa\\\"\\u003ePruitt \\u0026amp; Adlin, 2006\\u003c/a\\u003e).\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eFrom their inception in the late 1980s, refinement in the early 1990s (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_015_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac15Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eCooper, A. (2004). \\u003citalic\\u003eThe inmates are running the asylum: Why high-tech products drive us crazy and how to restore the sanity\\u003c/italic\\u003e (2nd ed.). Indianapolis: Pearson Higher Education.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eCooper\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2004\\u