data granularity in user segmentation. Yet, this is an issue that is practically important and theoretically interesting. Notably, customer segmentation and granularity are discussed by \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_013_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac13Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eClaycamp, H. J., \\u0026amp; Massy, W. F. (1968). A theory of market segmentation. \\u003citalic\\u003eJournal of Marketing Research\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e5\\u003c/italic\\u003e(4), 388\u2013394.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eClaycamp\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eH. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eMassy\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eW. F.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e1968\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eA theory of market segmentation\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eJournal of Marketing Research\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e5\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e4\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e388\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e394\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_013_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac13Aa\\\"\\u003eClaycamp and Massy (1968)\\u003c/a\\u003e who found aggregation beneficial for marketing practice. The optimal segmentation of user groups has also been pursued in Computer Science without a definitive solution (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_