0_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac70Aa\\\"\\u003eTarka, 2019\\u003c/a\\u003e). Also, the traditional persona creation process has typically relied on data collection methods, such as surveys or focus groups (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_047_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac47Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eNielsen, L. (2019). \\u003citalic\\u003ePersonas\u2014user focused design\\u003c/italic\\u003e (2nd ed.). London: Springer.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eNielsen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eL.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2019\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003ePersonas\u2014user focused design\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e2nd ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eLondon\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eSpringer\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_047_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac47Aa\\\"\\u003eNielsen, 2019\\u003c/a\\u003e; \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_053_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac53Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003ePruitt, J., \\u0026amp; Grudin, J. (2003). Personas: practice and theory. \\u003citalic\\u003eProceedings of the 2003 Conference on Designing for User Experiences\\u003c/italic\\u003e (pp. 1\u201315). New York, NY: ACM. doi:\\u003cpub-id style=\\\"display:none;\\\"  pub-id-type=\\\"doi\\\"\\u003e10.1145/997078.997089\\u003c/pub-id\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\