ame\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAn\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eKwak\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eH.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS. G.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2018\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eAre personas done? Evaluating their usefulness in the age of digital analytics\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003ePersona Studies\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e4\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e47\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e65\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_058_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac58Aa\\\"\\u003eSalminen et al., 2018\\u003c/a\\u003e), this has led to the employment of mainly qualitative data analysis approaches that lead end users to question if the underlying persona data is representative, updated, or valid of the actual user population. However, the advent of data-driven personas in the age of easily available analytics data has led to a recognition of the possible integration of the personas (to give a human face) and analytics (to provide actionable numbers and precision).\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eRemarkably, with the combining of personas and analytics, the strengths of each approach help offset the deficiencies of the other. Conceptually, personas are easy for people to understand and generate empathy for the user, but personas are perceived as not granular and not actionable. Analytics data can be granular and actionable, but analytics can be cumbersome for employment and difficult for end users to comprehend. Nonetheless, the combination of both leverages the strengths and limits the weakness of each, as shown in (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_057_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac57Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eSalminen, J., Guan, K., Nielsen, L., Jung, S., Chowdhury, S. A., \\u0026amp; Jansen, B. J. (2020, July 19). A Template for Data-Driven Personas: Analyzing 31 Quantitatively Oriented Persona Profiles. \\u003citalic\\u003eIn Proceedings of the 22nd International Conference on Human-Computer Interaction (HCII\u201920)\\u003c/italic\\u003e. In-press.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"confproc\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSalminen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eGuan\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eK.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eNielsen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eL.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJung\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\