iven-names\\\"\\u003eS. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2008\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003ePredicting online channel use for an online and print magazine: A case study\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eInternet Research\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e18\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e3\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e266\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e285\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_066_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac66Aa\\\"\\u003eSrisuwan \\u0026amp; Barnes, 2008\\u003c/a\\u003e). The theoretical foundation of these use cases is the focus of the 4Cs (i.e., clarity, credibility, consistency, and competitiveness) of marketing communications (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_027_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac27Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eJobber, D., \\u0026amp; Fahy, J. (2009). Foundations of marketing (3rd ed.). Maidenhead: McGraw-Hill Higher Education.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJobber\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eD.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eFahy\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2009\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eFoundations of marketing\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e3rd ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eMaidenhead\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eMcGraw-Hill Higher Education\\u003c/publisher-