_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac24Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eJansen, B. J., \\u0026amp; Schuster, S. (2011). Bidding on the buying funnel for sponsored search and keyword advertising. \\u003citalic\\u003eJournal of Electronic Commerce Research\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e12\\u003c/italic\\u003e(1), 1\u201318.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSchuster\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eS.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2011\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eBidding on the buying funnel for sponsored search and keyword advertising\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eJournal of Electronic Commerce Research\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e12\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e1\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e1\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e18\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_024_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac24Aa\\\"\\u003eJansen \\u0026amp; Schuster, 2011\\u003c/a\\u003e) and dividing budget across campaigns and ad sets. Using methods, such as keyword analysis (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_025_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac25Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eJansen, B. J., Spink, A., \\u0026amp; Saracevic, T. (2000). Real life, real users, and real needs: A study and analysis of user queries on the web. \\u003citalic\\u003eInformation Processing \\u0026amp; Management\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e36\\u003c/italic\\u003e(2), 207\u2013227.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"journal\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eJansen\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eB. J.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSpink\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eA.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eSaracevic\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eT.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2000\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003carticle-title\\u003eReal life, real users, and real needs: A study and analysis of user queries on the web\\u003c/article-title\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eInformation Processing \\u0026amp; Management\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cvolume\\u003e36\\u003c/volume\\u003e\\u003cissue\\u003e2\\u003c/issue\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"fpage\\\"\\u003e207\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"lpage\\\"\\u003e227\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_025_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac25Aa\\\"\\u003eJansen, Spink, \\u0026amp; Saracevic, 2000\\u003c/a\\u003e) and netnography (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_035_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac35Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003eKozinets, R. V. (2002). The field behind the screen: Using netnography for marketing research in online communities. \\u003citalic\\u003eJournal of Marketing Research\\u003c/italic\\u003e, \\u003citalic\\u003e39\\u003c/italic\\u003e(1), 61\u201372.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  p