ent the employment of APG relative to our research objective of demonstrating how personas access online data to provide value for business decision-makers, with a focus on levels of granularity.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/sec\\u003e\\u003csec id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_s_003_s_003_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b2b4Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003e3.3\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cdiv\\u003eConceptual Understanding of APG\\u003c/div\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eData-driven persona systems, similar to APG, provide the opportunity for a full-stack data methodological approach discussed earlier, with an integration of data from the customer-level through conceptual at the persona-level (see \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_006_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b2b4b3Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 6\\u003c/a\\u003e).\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cfigure id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_006_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b2b4b3Aa\\\" position=\\\"float\\\" fig-type=\\\"figure\\\"\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eFigure 6\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cfigCaption\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eAn illustration of full-stack data integration within a persona-analytics system, from the data-level to the analytics-level to the conceptual-level with the personas.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/figCaption\\u003e\\u003cimg xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"graphic/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_006.jpg\\\" src=\\\"https://sciendo-parsed-data-feed.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/6005bbb5e797941b18f255fd/j_dim-2020-0005_fig_006.jpg?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Date=20211130T193832Z\\u0026amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Expires=18000\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Credential=AKIA6AP2G7AKDOZOEZ7H%2F20211130%2Feu-central-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\\u0026amp;X-Amz-Signature=c64c5aa63685b5c9516c3df65f7b08db8f07a2557710bba77590494509a334a7\\\" class=\\\"mw-100\\\"\\u003e\\u003c/img\\u003e\\u003c/figure\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eAs illustrated in \\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_006_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b2b4b3Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 6\\u003c/a\\u003e, the data-driven persona system employs the base level user-data that the system algorithms act upon, converting this user data into useful information. The product of this algorithmic processing is actionable measures and metrics concerning the user population (i.e., weights, probabilities, percentages, etc.) of the kind that one would usually encounter in industry-standard analytics platforms. The subsequent level of abstraction engaged by the system is to use this analytics data, with the corresponding meta-tagged content, such as names and photos, to create sets of personas profiles at the conceptual level. This results in a data-driven persona system adept at presenting user insights at diverse levels of granularity, with levels that are both appropriately integrated to the task. We now discuss these three levels.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003csec id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_s_003_s_003_s_001_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b2b4b5Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003e3.3.1\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cdiv\\u003eConceptual Level (Personas)\\u003c/div\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe uppermost level of abstraction is the set of personas generated by the system from the user data, with a default setting of ten personas for APG, although the system user can adjust this number to generate fewer or more personas) (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_007_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b2b4b5b3Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 7\\u003c/a\\u003e). The persona profile (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"fig\\\" rid=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_fig_007_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab1b2b4b5b3Aa\\\"\\u003eFigure 7\\u003c/a\\u003e) has most of the standard attributes that one finds in the traditional flat persona profiles (e.g., name, photo, etc.); however, the data-driven persona is derived from real online user data, which addresses many of the major criticisms of flat personas created manually that they\\n\\u003clist list-type=\\\"custom\\\"\\u003e\\u003clist-item\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003ea)\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eare not based on quantitative user data (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\"  id=\\\"j_dim-2020-0005_ref_052_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac52Aa\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"mixed-citation\\\"\\u003ePruitt, J., \\u0026amp; Adlin, T. (2006). \\u003citalic\\u003eThe Persona Lifecycle: Keeping People in Mind Throughout Product Design\\u003c/italic\\u003e (1st ed.). San Francisco, CA: Morgan Kaufmann.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"element-citation\\\"  publication-type=\\\"book\\\" publication-format=\\\"print\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003ePruitt\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eJ.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"name\\\"\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"surname\\\"\\u003eAdlin\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"given-names\\\"\\u003eT.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cyear\\u003e2006\\u003c/year\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"source\\\"\\u003eThe Persona Lifecycle: Keeping People in Mind Throughout Product Design\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cedition\\u003e1st ed.\\u003c/edition\\u003e\\u003cspan class=\\\"publisher-loc\\\"\\u003eSan Francisco, CA\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003cpublisher-name\\u003eMorgan Kaufmann\\u003c/publisher-name\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/span\\u003e' href=\\\"#j_dim-2020-0005_ref_052_w2aab3b7c26b1b6b1ab2ac52Aa\\\"\\u003ePruitt \\u0026amp; Adlin, 2006\\u003c/a\\u003e)\u2014for data-driven personas, the data is immediately underlying the personas and can be viewed by the end user,\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003c/list-item\\u003e\\u003clist-item\\u003e\\u003clabel\\u003eb)\\u003c/label\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003etake too long to create for fast-pace industries such as online content creation (\\u003ca data-toggle='tooltip'  ref-type=\\\"bibr\\\" data-tooltip-info='\\u003cspan class=\\\"ref\\\" 